tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: The patient shows elevated serum creatinine, indicating impaired renal function, and significant proteinuria, suggesting possible glomerular pathology. Urine findings (cloudy, brown, low specific gravity, ketones, glucose, bilirubin) further support renal involvement and possible metabolic derangement. Hypoglycemia and low HbA1c may reflect poor nutritional status or overtreatment of diabetes. Recommend urgent nephrology evaluation and further assessment for underlying renal and metabolic disorders.
